FBIS3-37824 "drsov036_r_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-036 Document Type:Daily Report 23 Feb 1994 Azerbaijan Preview of Aliyev's Visit to Britain Agenda of Visit Detailed NC2202174494 Baku Radio Baku International Service in Azeri 1300 GMT 22 Feb 94 NC2202174494 Baku Radio Baku International Service Language: Azeri Article Type:BFN [Text] President Geydar Aliyev's visit to Britain began today and will end on 25 February. Aliyev will hold talks on issues relating to the mutual relations between Azerbaijan and Britain, the way to end the dispute between Azerbaijan and Armenia, and economic issues. Afshin Mekhtiyev, a representative of the Azerbaijani Foreign Ministry, briefed journalists in Baku on Aliyev's visit. Aliyev will hold talks with Prime Minister John Major in London. He will also hold talks with other government officials and meet British businessmen. According to Mekhtiyev, several documents will be drawn up on bilateral cooperation in the political, economic, scientific, and educational fields. Mekhtiyev said he may also discuss cooperation between the Azerbaijani State Oil Company and British Petroleum on oil extraction.
